Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of ten (10) years.  That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.
The court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant has 274 days credit.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Have no contact with any known drug users or dealers;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) pay restitution of $691.74 to the Manitowoc County Sheriffs Department from case no: 18 CF 12.  Court orders restitution to be taken from the defendants prison accounts;
9) DNA sample ordered.
Minutes.
